A Dutch mother has defied safety warnings and travelled to Syria in disguise to rescue her daughter from the Islamic State. 

Wearing a burka, the woman from Maastricht - named only as Monique - crossed from Turkey into the Syrian city of Raqqa to save her daughter Aicha, 19. 

Aicha had appealed to her mother for help last month after converting to Islam and marrying Omar Yilmaz, a notorious Dutch jihadi.

